

=Bio=

"Architect, maker and writer, my work starts from a background of DIY practices and cultures.

I focus on design as a process and as an evolving system reflecting social, technological and economical phenomena.

After having spent many years in the field of architecture and planning between Milan and Berlin, I am now the curator and manager of the new Fablab at the MUSE Science Museum.

I write on computational design culture for Digicult and Doppiozero and other italian magazines of cultural critics. As recent interest, I investigate on the intertwined condition occurring among Design, Art and Science both through the activities of the MuSe Fablab and the column #Advancity that I curate for Doppiozero and Digicult."
(https://fossa.inria.fr/speakers/)


